a community for 6 yearsMODERATORSEmeritus Minister MentorEmeritus Senior MinisterMinister of Foreign Affairs and Sailing1-900-CONFESSION1171819 ()submitted 3 days ago by Mee Pok ManI'll start the ball rolling with 2 examples.
Sembcorp Waste Truck Driver. Saw this in the paper the other day, the guy earns $3k a month. Good enough to support his family of 2 kids and a wife.
Huge Crane Operator. I don't know the proper term for it, but it's one of those giant-ass cranes and not the smaller kind. Think of the biggest ones you see and that's it. It can get you $4-$4.5k if I'm not wrong. But such jobs requires a fair bit of experience and some technical expertise, so its something you have to be trained for. Also the chances of emergency toilet breaks on the job are slim to none.
Working at these jobs don't require much paper qualifications, and are decent enough for a person to apply for loans and buy their own house, sustain their own family. Are there any others like that?
