0 points1 point2 points 3 days ago  0 points1 point2 points 3 days agoTruck driver. The guys who drive trucks that move sand from the Tampines to other areas in Singapore make about 80-120 bucks a trip. A friend's brother once made close to 4k in a month. Averages about 3k.
2 points3 points4 points 1 day ago*  2 points3 points4 points 1 day ago*I concur on the truck driver. Especially Trailer driver (Class 4).
Prices I have seen so far with basic pay of $0-600/mth,
Each delivery is around $35-$65 (depending on the chassis size and item)
Post-delivery, returning of an empty chassis is around $15-$20 (again, dependent on size; for example a low bed, wide chassis is usually worth more)
Moving of chassis in loading bay/warehouse is $10-$20/hr
Waiting for loading $10/hr (depends on the company. If the driver has no basic pay, waiting time is paid for)
It can go higher but I ain't telling you how high it can go. These are the current average.
If you make about the minimum 3 trips per day, you can net about 2-3k easily. Usually if you do 3 trips, you'll probably finish work at 5 or 6pm if there are no waiting during delivery.
But the cons are:
Reporting time can start as early as 7.30am but work starts at 8.30am cause the factories open at that time. You got to be early to catch as many jobs as possible! Early bird catches the juiciest worm!
Some construction site requires a lot of waiting! Waiting during delivery is not paid! So sometimes drivers do leave chassis at the side of the road and leave if it takes too damn long. Hence why you'll see some abandoned chassis at the side of construction sites.
It can get very tiring especially if you're driving the old truck with gears, no power steering and very very limp suspension. However nowadays, many companies has trailer trucks that comes with auto gear and power steering! So you might get lucky.
If the controller hates you or you don't get along with him/her, say bye bye to your rice bowl.
Why do the low and wide bed chassis cost more? Cause you can't drive on the expressway. Going from Tuas to Changi? Good luck navigating through neighbourhoods. Want to go on expressways? You got to pay for Cisco escorts and usually companies don't unless it's urgent.
There are many more details but if you have some self-discipline and are hard working, I have seen drivers earning upwards of 6k. One PRC guy broke record by earning 7+k. I swear that guy doesn't sleep or something.
Oh by the way, sand trucks are definitely not where the money is at because sand trucks involves a lot a lot of waiting. Time is money! Trailers trailers trailers!
Source: I work with trailer drivers. Control 'em like little toy cars.
